					<head>Commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the book of Job (fragments).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jrb">Hebrew, Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="102v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Iyov </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש איוב</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="en">Japheth ben Ali, ha-Levi,‏ active 10th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/54984961" xml:lang="he">יפת בן עלי, הלוי </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The volume contains Yefet's Arabic commentary on Job 1:1-5:25, 6:1-9:19, 9:21-22 and parts of the introduction.</p>
								<p>The pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, accompanied by a verse by verse Arabic translation, is embodied.</p>
								<p>Of the Hebrew text the following parts are preserved: 1:1-5:26, 6:1-9:19, 9:22.</p>
								<p>The readings of the קרי are marked in the margins.</p>
								<p>This volume has been revised, omissions being supplied and mistkaes corrected, in the margin.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; square and semi-cursive script of the early 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex</support>
								<extent>102 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>188</height>
										<width>135</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>145</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>102 folios (+ 2 paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>12 quires, originally of 10 leaves each (except the 3rd which has 11 leaves).</p>
									<p>Quires 1-2, 8, 11-12 are imperfect.</p>
									<p>The quires are signed with Hebrew letters and Arabic words on the upper margin of the first page, and with Hebrew letters on the lower margin of the last page.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Lacunae after folios: 3, 63, 101.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="15" writtenLines="15">
									<p>The numbers of the chapters have been added by a later hand.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on evey verso, partially invisible due to tight binding.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
